    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "To give a bit of background on this, having validator account metrics on by default causes high data carnality which can inflate retention sizes in tsdb. This is only a concern to users running many validators. So the current behavior is working as intended but it does have some user confusion. \r\n\r\nI'm going to mark this as a feature request to invert the flag functionality. Power users can opt-out of validator account metrics rather than having most users opt-in.",
